      "HRRT sent for metallurgical evaluation"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 19, 2024, at 13:30 hrs, during BOP deployment and riser running operations on the Valaris DS-18 drillship, riser joint #31 was being hoisted approximately 30 feet above the rig floor when the riser cart shuttle failed to freewheel due to a loose brake wire causing a fuse to blow. The hydraulic brake did not release, causing the riser flange to be pulled out of the cart shuttle. The Cameron Hydraulic Riser Running Tool (HRRT) removable shank mandrel parted under shock load, and the riser joint fell back onto the riser cart, damaging the skate tailing arms, skate lift bucket, HRRT, and riser joint floatation. No injuries occurred. Estimated damage: $418,000.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Improve job template detail on inspection of all load path components of the HRRT"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "riser cart shuttle did not free-wheel",
      "loose wire on the riser cart shuttle brake",
      "fuse to blow",
      "hydraulic brake did not release",
      "HRRT removable shank mandrel parted",
      "shock impact from the riser falling",
      "Job template is not detailed enough"
    ]
  },
